-- Israel Chemicals Gains as Potash Corp. Seeks to Raise Stake
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2011-12-19T15:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/israel-chemicals-gains-as-calcalist-says-potash-to-raise-stake.html
Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL)  rose for the
third time in four days after the Finance Ministry said that
 Potash (POT)  Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc. is seeking to raise its stake
in the company that extracts minerals from the  Dead Sea .  Israel Chemicals gained 2.4 percent, the most since Dec.
15, to 36.70 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. The
shares have declined 40 percent this year, while Israel’s
benchmark stock index, the TA-25, is down 17 percent.  Israel Corp., which according to data compiled by Bloomberg
owns a 52 percent stake in Israel Chemicals, climbed 2.8
percent.  Potash requested permission from Israel’s Finance Ministry
to increase its stake to 25 percent from 13.9 percent, the
ministry said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
